snippet.textDisplay:
I'm sorry to be such a downer, but while you are in Hawaii relaxing, currently in Australia, myself and many others are undergoing a bushfire crisis. Up to 150,000 hectares of land has been damaged and 6.3 million hectares affected, which is A LOT more than both the Amazon and California fires combined. Even where I live in Melbourne (one of the main cities) it is difficult because the whole sky is filled with smoke and is becoming very difficult to breathe in. There is even a place in Victoria which went completely black the other day like a light bulb due to the fires. What I ask of each of you and you, Colleen, is to help out as much as you can, and spread this message, as the more people know about this and take action the better. Even just sharing this message around is more than what our own prime minister is doing, which is being on a nice relaxing holiday in Hawaii (where you are) when OUR COUNTRY IS BURNING DOWN! If you are in the mood and are able to, it would be very much appreciated if you could donate to the following websites and support the people and animals affected by the fires:
NSW Rural Fire Service: https://rfs.nsw.gov.au/volunteer/support-your-local-brigade

Even where I live in Melbourne (one of the main cities) it is difficult because the whole sky is filled with smoke and is becoming very difficult to breathe in.
